<?xml version="1.0"?>
<html>
  <problem>
    <title> CheckPoint: Work by a Pendulum</title>
    
      <p>A pendulum consists of a small ball that has a mass m suspended on a light long string of length l. Initially, the pendulum is held at rest so that the string is taut and makes an angle \(\theta\) with the vertical. The pendulum is then released. 

</p>
      <br/>
    
    <parameter default="2" description="Maximum Number of Tries" type="int_pos" name="maxtries" loncapaid="11"/>
    <br/>
    
      <p>
Part 1. 
By the time the pendulum passes through the equilibrium position, what is the amount of work done by the force of tension on the ball?
</p>
    
    <part loncapaid="12">
      <br/>
      <multiplechoiceresponse max="10" direction="vertical" randomize="no" loncapaid="13" type="MultipleChoice">
        <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
          <choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="false">
                  \( mgl \cos \theta\)
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="false">
                  \( mgl(1- \cos \theta)\)
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="false">
                  \( mgl \sin \theta\)
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="false">
                  \(mgl (1- \sin \theta)\)
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil5" correct="true">

zero
          </choice>
        </choicegroup>
      </multiplechoiceresponse>
    </part>
    <part loncapaid="14">
      
        <p>
Part 2. 
By the time the pendulum passes through the equilibrium position, what is the amount of work done by the force of gravity on the ball?
</p>
      
      <br/>
      <multiplechoiceresponse max="10" direction="vertical" randomize="no" loncapaid="15" type="MultipleChoice">
        <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
          <choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="false">
                  \( mgl \cos \theta\)
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="true">
                  \( mgl(1- \cos \theta)\)
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="false">
                  \( mgl \sin \theta\)
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="false">
                  \(mgl (1- \sin \theta)\)
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil5" correct="false">

zero
          </choice>
        </choicegroup>
      </multiplechoiceresponse>
    </part>
  </problem>
</html>
